data.Name: The Jellied Eels
data.Bio: The Jellied Eels are an English comedy band consisting of lead vocalist Charlie Squire, guitarists Dominic Ryan and Ben Lyons, bass guitarist Sam Mills and drummer James Palmer. The band was formed in 2004 in Bramley, Surrey. The band is famous for their controversial songs, most notably: The Pedophile Song and White Cop. Review taken from the Guardian newspaper. Well what is there to say......perhaps the greatest band ever. They said it was impossible. Read more on Last.fm
